Definition 2.1. [dk, 7.4] A map $f:\mathcal{C}\rightarrow\mathcal{D}$ in $\mathcal{SC}_{\mathcal{O}}$ is free if (1) $f$ is a monomorphism, (2) if $\ast$ denotes the free product, then in each simplicial dimension $k$, the category $\mathcal{D}_{k}$ admits a unique free factorization $\mathcal{D}_{k}=f(\mathcal{C}_{k})\ast\mathcal{F}_{k}$, where $\mathcal{F}_{k}$ is a free category, and (3) for each $k\geq 0$, all degeneracies of generators of $\mathcal{F}_{k}$ are generators of $\mathcal{F}_{k+1}$.
